.TH "llc_build_and_send_xid_pkt" 9 "llc_build_and_send_xid_pkt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
llc_build_and_send_xid_pkt \- XID interface for upper layers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" llc_build_and_send_xid_pkt
.BI "(struct llc_sap *sap "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "u8 *dmac "  ","
.BI "u8 dsap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sap" 12
sap to use
.IP "skb" 12
packet to send
.IP "dmac" 12
destination mac address
.IP "dsap" 12
destination sap

This function is called when upper layer wants to send a XID pdu.
Returns 0 for success, 1 otherwise.
